.TH PAM_SGFP 8 "2026-03-04" "sgpam 0.1.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
pam_sgfp \- PAM module for SecuGen fingerprint authentication
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B auth
.RI [ sufficient | required ]
.B pam_sgfp.so
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pam_sgfp
is a PAM authentication module that captures a live fingerprint from
a SecuGen U20 reader and matches it against templates previously
enrolled with
.BR sg_enroll (1).
.PP
The module supports multi-finger enrollment: all templates for a user
are loaded and tried in sequence.
Authentication succeeds on the first matching template.
.PP
Templates are discovered by glob pattern:
.IR /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/ username _*.tpl
(finger-specific templates) and
.IR /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/ username .tpl
(legacy single-finger template).
Both formats are supported for backward compatibility.
.PP
If no template exists for the authenticating user, the module returns
.B PAM_USER_UNKNOWN
so that a subsequent PAM rule (typically password authentication) can
take over.
This enables a graceful fallback: enrolled users authenticate by
fingerprint, while unenrolled users are silently passed through to
password.
.PP
The module prompts via the PAM conversation function with the names
of enrolled fingers, for example:
.RB \(lq "Place finger on scanner (right-index, left-thumb)..." \(rq.
For legacy single-finger templates the generic prompt
.RB \(lq "Place finger on scanner..." \(rq
is shown instead.
Capture uses a 10-second timeout.
Matching uses security level
.B SL_NORMAL
(match score >= 80/199).
.SH MODULE TYPES PROVIDED
.B auth
.SH RETURN VALUES
.TP
.B PAM_SUCCESS
The live fingerprint matched an enrolled template.
.TP
.B PAM_AUTH_ERR
Authentication failed.
This covers: match failure against all templates, capture timeout,
SDK initialisation errors, device not found, or invalid username.
.TP
.B PAM_USER_UNKNOWN
No enrolled template was found for the user.
When
.B pam_sgfp.so
is configured as
.BR sufficient ,
PAM skips it and tries the next module in the stack.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/lib/security/pam_sgfp.so
The shared library installed by the package.
.TP
.I /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/
Directory containing per-user fingerprint templates (mode 0700, root only).
.TP
.IR /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/ username _ finger-name .tpl
Enrolled template for a specific finger (e.g.,
.IR alice_right-index.tpl ).
Mode 0600.
.TP
.IR /etc/security/sg_fingerprints/ username .tpl
Legacy single-finger template.
Still recognised for backward compatibility.
.SH SECURITY
.TP
.B Match threshold
Uses
.B SL_NORMAL
security level, requiring a match score of at least 80 out of 199.
.TP
.B Template format
Templates use SecuGen SG400 format with AES encryption.
.TP
.B Capture quality floor
Images scoring below 40/100 quality are rejected before matching.
.TP
.B Path traversal protection
Usernames are validated against a strict character set before
constructing the template file path.
Slashes and special characters are rejected.
.TP
.B Image dimension guard
Abnormal image dimensions (0 or >4096 in either axis) are rejected
to prevent buffer overflow.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
All messages are logged via
.BR syslog (3)
with facility
.BR LOG_AUTH .
.TP
.B "pam_sgfp: fingerprint accepted for user \(aq%s\(aq (template %d/%d)"
.RB ( LOG_INFO )
Authentication succeeded.
The template index indicates which enrolled finger matched.
.TP
.B "pam_sgfp: fingerprint rejected for user \(aq%s\(aq (%d templates tried)"
.RB ( LOG_NOTICE )
The live fingerprint did not match any enrolled template.
.TP
.B "pam_sgfp: no enrolled fingerprint for user \(aq%s\(aq"
.RB ( LOG_NOTICE )
No template file found; module returns
.BR PAM_USER_UNKNOWN .
.TP
.B "pam_sgfp: capture failed for \(aq%s\(aq"
.RB ( LOG_NOTICE )
The scanner timed out or the finger was removed before capture completed.
.TP
.B "pam_sgfp: SGFPM_OpenDevice failed \(em scanner connected?"
.RB ( LOG_ERR )
The SecuGen U20 reader was not detected on any USB port.
.TP
.B "pam_sgfp: invalid username rejected (path traversal?)"
.RB ( LOG_WARNING )
The PAM username contained disallowed characters.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS sudo authentication
Add to
.I /etc/pam.d/sudo
before the existing password rule:
.PP
.RS
.nf
auth  sufficient  pam_sgfp.so
auth  include     system-auth
.fi
.RE
.SS Display manager (SDDM)
Add to
.IR /etc/pam.d/sddm :
.PP
.RS
.nf
auth  sufficient  pam_sgfp.so
auth  include     system-login
.fi
.RE
.SS Console login
Add to
.IR /etc/pam.d/login :
.PP
.RS
.nf
auth  sufficient  pam_sgfp.so
auth  include     system-local-login
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sg_enroll (1),
.BR pam (8),
.BR pam.d (5),
.BR pam.conf (5)
